core.gui.config.controls.title: Choose a configuration to change:
core.gui.config.joystick.error: ERROR: MTS could not initialize the control system!  This is likely due to a device mis-representing itself as a joystick to Java.  Mice have been known to have this issue, especially Corsair mice, so try a different mouse.  You may also try un-plugging your mouse, and then opening this GUI to re-poll the joysticks.  This won't make controls work on boot, but can be used if you only have one mouse.
core.gui.config.joystick.disabled: ERROR: The control system locked up when MTS tried to initialize it.  This is likely a driver issue, and happens for some reason on some machines.  The root cause is not known, but if you find out how to make this erorr go away, let us know!  For now, joysick support will be disabled.
core.gui.config.joystick.name: Name:
core.gui.config.joystick.choosemap: Choose what gets mapped to this button.
core.gui.config.joystick.calibrate1: Move axis until numbers stop changing.
core.gui.config.joystick.calibrate2: Then hit confirm to save settings.
core.gui.packmissing.title: !ERROR!
core.gui.packmissing.text: MTS has detected that it has been started without a content pack.  This will result in NO vehicles being present!  If you do NOT have a content pack yet installed, please see the Curse page for this mod for a link to one.  If you DID download a pack ensure that it is the same place as all your other mods.  If the pack is in that location, and you are still seeing this message, ensure you are running the correct pack version.
core.interact.key.bind: Key bound to vehicle.  Ready for locking/unlocking use.
core.interact.key.notowner: This key is not for any vehicle, and only the owner of this vehicle may make new keys!
core.interact.key.wrongkey: This key does not go to this vehicle!
core.interact.fuelpump.toofar: The pump is too far away from the vehicle.  The pump should be no more than 16 blocks away.
core.interact.fuelpump.wrongtype: This pump does not contain the same fuel type as what is in the vehicle.
core.interact.fuelpump.wrongengines: The contents in this pump is not a valid fuel for the engines in the vehicle.  Check the manual for details.
core.interact.road.alreadyconnected: This road segment is already connected to another road.
core.interact.road.lanemismatchfirst: The number of lanes at the road segment clicked first does not match the number of lanes for this road.
core.interact.road.lanemismatchsecond: The number of lanes at the road segment just clicked does not match the number of lanes for this road.
core.interact.road.blocked: No space found to place the master block for this road.  Try a less crowded area?
core.interact.road.same: Both the first point and the second point clicked are the same block.  Reset and try again.
core.interact.road.toofar: The two points clicked are too far apart.  Either find closer points, or increase the distance in the config file.
core.interact.road.blockingblocks: There are blocks blocking the placement of this road.  Break the highlighted red ones, and then click the blue master road block to continue.
core.interact.jerrycan.empty: This jerrycan is empty and cannot fuel this vehicle.
core.interact.jerrycan.wrongtype: This jerrycan does not contain the same liquid as what is in the vehicle.
core.interact.jerrycan.wrongengines: The contents in this jerrycan is not a valid fuel for the engines in the vehicle.  Check the manual for details.
core.interact.jerrycan.toofull: This vehicle is already full of fuel.  You cannot add any more.
core.interact.jerrycan.success: Added 1000mb of fluid to this vehicle.
core.interact.vehicle.owned: You are not the owner of this vehicle and therefore cannot change it or its parts!
core.interact.vehicle.needkey: You must have the key of this vehicle to start it!
core.interact.vehicle.nospace: There is not enough space to place down this vehicle here.
core.interact.vehicle.cantremoveinventory: You cannot remove this part because it is not empty!
core.interact.jumpercable.firstlink: Linking first engine to jumper cable.
core.interact.jumpercable.linkdropped: The two engines have moved too far apart from one another.  Breaking link.
core.interact.jumpercable.powerequal: The two engines now have the same battery level.  Breaking link.
core.interact.jumpercable.alreadylinked: This engine is already linked to another engine and cannot be linked.
core.interact.jumpercable.toofar: The two engines are too far away.  They should be no further than 16 blocks apart.
core.interact.jumpercable.samevehicle: The two engines are on the same vehicle.  That's not going to work well..
core.interact.fuelhose.firstlink: Source tank linked to fuel hose.
core.interact.fuelhose.linkdropped: The linked tanks have moved too far apart from one another.  Breaking link.
core.interact.fuelhose.alreadylinked: This tank is already linked to another tank and cannot be linked.
core.interact.fuelhose.toofar: The two tanks are too far away.  They should be no further than 16 blocks apart.
core.interact.fuelhose.differentfluids: The source and destination tanks do not contain the same fluid and cannot be linked.
core.interact.trailer.notfound: No trailers were found anywhere near this vehicle.
core.interact.trailer.toofar: The trailer is too far from the vehicle.
core.interact.trailer.wronghitch: This vehicle does not have the correct hitch for this trailer.
core.interact.trailer.mismatch: A hitch was found that is close enough to connect, but was not the correct type.  Also, a matching hitch was found, but it was too far to connect.  Are you trying to use the wrong hitch?
core.interact.trailer.alreadytowed: The only nearby vehicle is already being towed.
core.interact.trailer.feedbackloop: The only nearby vehicles are being towed by this vehicle, towing would result in an infinite towing loop.
core.iteminfo.jerrycan.fill: Fill this can by right-clicking a fuel pump.
core.iteminfo.jerrycan.drain: Fill a vehicle by right-clicking with a full can.
core.sytstem.soundslot: IMMERSIVE VEHICLES ERROR: Tried to play a sound, but was told no sound slots were available. Some mod is taking up all the slots. If you have Immersive Railroading, set override sound channels to false in that mod's config. If running GregTech, set maxNumSounds to a lower value in that mod's config. Dynamic Surrondings and Optifine also may cause issues. Apply fixes, or complain to those mod's authors. Sounds will not play.

mts.fuelhose.name: Fuel Hose
mts.fuelhose.description:
Use on a vehicle tank to select.
Use on second tank or vehicle to link.
Hose will transfer liquids from tank 1 to selected.
Hose will stop when tank 1 is empty, selected is full or if tank 1 and selected are too far away.

mts.jumpercable.name: Jumper Cables
mts.jumpercable.description:
Use on an engine to select.
Use on second engine to link.
Linked engines will exchange power.
Engines will un-link when power is even or if they get too far away.

mts.jumperpack.name: Jumper Pack
mts.jumperpack.description: Use on a vehicle to charge battery to max level.

mts.key.name: Key
mts.key.description: Because leaving a car unlocked in Minecraft is like leaving it unlocked in GTA...

mts.paintgun.name: Paint Gun
mts.paintgun.description:
Use on a vehicle, a part, decor, or sign to change its color.
Note: Not all things you can click will have multiple colors.

mts.partscanner.name: Part Scanner
mts.partscanner.description:
Hover over a part box to see what can be placed at that slot.
Sneak while using to cycle slower.

mts.ticket.name: Ticket
mts.ticket.description:
Right-click on a vehicle to load nearby entities.
Right-click on a seat to load just that seat.
Sneak-click on a vehicle to unload all entities.
Note: Will not unload players.

mts.wrench.name: Wrench
mts.wrench.description:
Attack a vehicle part to remove it.
Sneak-attack a vehicle to remove entire vehicle.
Use on vehicle to change instruments.
Sneak-use on vehicle to change text.
Use on pole components to remove them.
Use on fuel pumps you placed to change prices.

mts.y2kbutton.name: Y2K Button
mts.y2kbutton.description:
Use in a world to turn off all vehicle engines, engage their parking brakes, and turn off their lights.
Only usable by admins.

auweschvebm.auweschveb_vehicle_a_yf22_dk.name: Darkez Air Defense YF-22
auweschvebm.auweschveb_vehicle_a_yf22_dk.description: As the 60s came to a close, and after the Aden Revolutionary war, military command in the ShSR realized the YF-20 was severely lacking. Poor low speed preformance, no carrier capability, and a rather primitive look-up only radar, it was clear a replacement was needed. the Yakunov-Felchlin Design beuro had solved the variable geometry problem, and the YF-22 Was oficcialy comissioned. Designed for hypersonic hit-and-run tactics the YF-22 makes for a poor dogfighter, but excellent when used in it's designed conditions.

auweschvebm.auweschveb_vehicle_a_yf40_bl.description: When the need was realized for a modern ground attack aircraft, the prestigious YF design beuro came with several options to fill this role, among others, an YF-22 aircraft without the radar, modern TV guidance systems, hardpoints on the wings, and a 6 barrelled 30mm cannon commonly found on ships. This was however generally considered a faliure, and the Buhoi Design Beuro had a solution more suited for the army's needs. The BU-40 Was born.

auweschvebm.auweschveb_vehicle_bt3_dkz.name: DKZ Armed Forces BT-60
auweschvebm.auweschveb_vehicle_bt3_dkz.description: While the BT-30 remains a good vehicle, there was severe limitations realized after the second great homeland war. The extensive mass deployment of chemical weapons in particular was something it could not handle, and it struggled with crossing uneven no-mans-land terrains so common on the southeastern front. This lead to the development of the BT-60. Prototypes for the BT-60 were in fact drawn up during the war, but the vehicle we know today, with the full NBC protetction, amphibious design and 8 axles did not roll off an assembly line before 1952.

blockyragecivil.brgolf1_black.name: Volkswagen Golf 1 [Black]
blockyragecivil.brgolf1_black.description: Production of the first Golf (internal name Typ 17) began in 1974. In the United States and Canada, it was produced under the brand name Volkswagen Rabbit, and in Latin America - Volkswagen Caribe. The first design of the Golf I was by Italian car designer Giorgiometto Giugiaro. In addition to the standard hatchback body, the Golf I was also produced as a convertible Golf Cabriolet (Typ 155). The release of Golf I convertibles stretched over the period from 1980 to 1993, turned to the recognition of the Golf III.

In the United States and Canada, it was produced under the brand name Volkswagen Rabbit, and in Latin America - Volkswagen Caribe. The first design of the Golf I was by Italian car designer Giorgiometto Giugiaro. In addition to the standard hatchback body, the Golf I was also produced as a convertible Golf Cabriolet (Typ 155). The release of Golf I convertibles stretched over the period from 1980 to 1993, turned to the recognition of the Golf III.

blockyragecivil.brmercedesw124_armygreen.name: Mercedes-Benz W124 [Army Green]
blockyragecivil.brmercedesw124_armygreen.description: In order to reduce the risk of declining attention to the new line of business class cars, Mercedes-Benz decided not to present the W124 series at the Frankfurt Motor Show in September 1984, where other brands also brought their own new or updated products. Instead, the new series of Mercedes-Benz W124 cars debuted at the Seville Motor Show (Spain) on November 5, 1984 in a sedan body with seven types of engines: 200E, 230E, 260E, 300E, 200D, 250D, 300D. Deliveries of orders to customers began in the first months of 1985.

blockyragecivil.brnissangtrr35_black.name: Nissan GTR R35 [Black]
blockyragecivil.brnissangtrr35_black.description: A sports car manufactured by Nissan Motor Company. Introduced as a production model at the Tokyo Motor Show on October 24, 2007, sales began in 2008 in Japan, followed by the US and Europe. Unlike its predecessors, which were produced only for JDM and delivered to the UK in a limited edition, there is a left-hand drive variant.

blockyragecivil.brporsche911930_armygree.name: Porsche 911 930 Turbo [Army Green]
blockyragecivil.brporsche911930_armygree.description: Porsche began experimenting with turbocharging technology in the late 1960s, developing a version of the 911 with a similar engine in 1972. The new car was originally developed for legal street racing, like the 1973 Carrera 2.7 RS. Porsche then decided to create a variant of the 911 with the highest possible finish, which could compete with the more expensive and exclusive Ferrari and Lamborghini than the standard 911.

blockyragecivil.brporsche911carrera_blac.name: Porsche 911 Carrera 1974 [Black]
blockyragecivil.brporsche911carrera_blac.description: The second generation is often informally referred to as G-modell after the letter of Porsche's annual model revision series, corresponding to the 1974 model year, the first year the second generation was launched. And despite the fact that the G-series ended its existence in calendar year 1974 and passed the baton to the H-series, and later, with the introduction of the seventeen-digit VIN in 1980, all the letter designations of the series were started all over again - in fact, any naturally aspirated Porsche can be called that. 911 second generation, produced until 1989.

blockyragecivil.brtoyotaaurionxv40_black.name: Toyota Aurion XV40 [Black]
blockyragecivil.brtoyotaaurionxv40_black.description: A mid-size car produced by Toyota in Australia and parts of Asia. Designated XV40, Toyota manufactured the first generation Aurion between 2006 and 2012 until it was fully replaced by the XV50 series. While Asian production of the XV50 series began in late 2011, Toyota's Australian operations did not take on production of the new model until 2012.

blockyragecivil.brtoyotacamryxv40_black.name: Toyota Camry XV40 [Black]
blockyragecivil.brtoyotacamryxv40_black.description: Produced from January 2006 to August 2011. Engineers from Japan, the USA, Australia and France worked on the creation of the car, versions of the Camry XV40 for different markets can vary significantly. In America and Japan, as well as in England, Toyota Camry is produced in a 2.4-liter version, in Southeast Asia - with a 2-liter engine. Technically delivered officially to Russia, Toyota Camry is the closest to the version for North America.

blockyrageheavy.brmanlc2017_black.name: MAN Lion's Coach 2017 [Black]
blockyrageheavy.brmanlc2017_black.description: The third generation MAN Lion's Coach was presented to the public at Busworld 2017 in Kortrijk on 24 October 2017. It features a completely new design compared to its predecessor, featuring a distinctive design that gives it a modern yet timeless look. The MAN Lion's Coach is now available in four lengths: from 12101 mm to 13091 mm as a two-axle vehicle and from 13361 mm to 13901 mm as a three-axle vehicle.

blockyrageheavy.brsolarisurbino12_b.description: Urbino is the name of a family of fully low-floor city buses that premiered in 1999. Solaris Urbino buses are a composition of stylish design, reliable and practical solutions and the guarantee of safety and eco-friendliness. Their unique look is defined by the characteristic curved windscreen. Not only is this a distinctive design element, but it also gives the driver better visibility of the nearside kerb, increasing the safety of passengers waiting at the bus stop. The Solaris Urbino bus with conventional drive is equipped with engines that meet the highly restrictive Euro 6 norm.

blockyragetaxi.brtoyotacamryxv40taxi_1.name: Toyota Camry XV40 Yellow Taxi
blockyragetaxi.brtoyotacamryxv40taxi_1.description: Produced from January 2006 to August 2011. Engineers from Japan, the USA, Australia and France worked on the creation of the car, versions of the Camry XV40 for different markets can vary significantly. In America and Japan, as well as in England, Toyota Camry is produced in a 2.4-liter version, in Southeast Asia - with a 2-liter engine. Technically delivered officially to Russia, Toyota Camry is the closest to the version for North America.

craftspeedengines.bmw3liters55gtsstage1.name: BMW 3.0 S55 GTS Engine [Stage 1 Upgrade]
craftspeedengines.bmw3liters55gtsstage1.description: More efficient water injection cooling combined with a bigger bore throttle body and ECU retune resulting in a bump of power to 650 hp.

craftspeedengines.camarosmallblockv8stag.name: Chevrolet 396ci small block [Stage 1 Upgrade]
craftspeedengines.camarosmallblockv8stag.description: An upgrade consisting of a better flow carburetor, as well as an addition of 5th gear and bigger compression.

craftspeedengines.chargerenginebugcatche.name: Dodge Magnum 440ci (7.2L) V8 Supercharged Engine
craftspeedengines.chargerenginebugcatche.description: Stock engine tuned up to 650 hp, a decent unit for street racing with the addition of 5th gear, fuel injection, a bugcatcher intake and a supercharger.

craftspeedengines.chargerenginehellephan.name: Mopar Hellephant Crate Engine [8-gear Automatic]
craftspeedengines.chargerenginehellephan.description: Mopar's monstrous creation, bearing 1000hp from a V8 and a gearbox from Challenger SRT Hellcat, making a perfect combination for all your restomod needs.

craftspeedengines.chargerenginehellephan.name: Mopar Hellephant Crate Engine [6-gear Manual]
craftspeedengines.chargerenginehellephan.description: Mopar's monstrous creation, bearing 1000hp from a V8 and a gearbox from Challenger SRT Hellcat, making a perfect combination for all your restomod needs.

craftspeedengines.chargerenginetoretto.name: Dodge Magnum 440ci (7.2L) V8 Supercharged (Level 2) Engine
craftspeedengines.chargerenginetoretto.description: Stock block, even with further upgrades, making 900hp out of a setup built entirely for raw power. Based on Dominic Toretto's Charger's engine from The Fast and The Furious.

craftspeedengines.civicengineitb.name: Honda B16B ITB Engine
craftspeedengines.civicengineitb.description: Extensively rebuilt stock B16B engine equipped with revised exhaust manifold, ECU remap and individual throttle bodies for better reaction for gas.

craftspeedengines.civicengineturbo.name: Honda B16B Turbocharged Engine
craftspeedengines.civicengineturbo.description: Classic Type R engine with a turbocharged strapped on. Makes 214 HP and has better low end response at the cost of maximum RPMs, as well as the general linearity of power delivery.

craftspeedengines.f40enginestage1.name: Ferrari F40 2.9 V8 Engine [Upgrade Stage 1]
craftspeedengines.f40enginestage1.description: Revised air flow, fuel injection system and a slight readjustment of turbocharging system to raise the power from stock 478 to current 550 HP.

craftspeedengines.f40enginestage2.name: Ferrari F40 2.9 V8 Engine [Upgrade Stage 2]
craftspeedengines.f40enginestage2.description: Removed restrictors and remapped ECU, adjusted to match F40 Competizione's 700 HP power mark.

dkzcivilianpack.rodimus_black.name: Black DKZ 410 Rodimus
dkzcivilianpack.rodimus_black.description:
The DKZ Design Team has released a new vehicle, to meet the fancy of those who want a loud and proud HotRod styled Roadster. Introducing the DKZ Industries 410 Rodimus! Featuring a removable hood for an open-engine design, fenderless body design, and a removable roof, this roadster is sure to tear up the canyon roads!

- UNU V8 Engine

dkzcivilianpack.fortina_1black.name: Black DKZ T-800 Fortina
dkzcivilianpack.fortina_1black.description:
Throwback to the 1950's, with the new DKZ Industries T-800 Fortina pickup truck! Built to haul as part of the DKZ T-Series, the  Fortina contains modern safety features within a classic 1950's look, including a wooden bed floor, removable stakebed, comfortable interior, and a steel ball hitch. This truck was built for the long haul.
 
Requires:
- UNU Standard Wheel (D14) [x4]
- UNU V8 Engine
 
Optional:
- UNU Crate (27-Slot) [x6]
- UNU Stakeside Bed

dkzcivilianpack.fortier_emma.name: Ford Towing Service DKZ T-850S Fortier
dkzcivilianpack.fortier_emma.description:
The DKZ Industries T-850S Fortier tow truck is a new addition to the T-Series, built as a Standard-Duty vehicle. Featuring the 850 Standard Budd Axle System, Dual-Arm Boom, Roof-Mounted Orange Gyrophare, Rubber Sling-tow Kit, two jerrycan racks, two fire extinguisher clips, and a spare standard tire, the Fortier is built to serve.
 
Requires:
- UNU V8 Engine
 
Optional:
- UNU Jerrycan [x2]
- UNU Fire Extinguisher [x2]

dkzcivilianpack.racetrailer_1black.description: The Flatbed Vehicle Transport Trailer is the perfect method for transporting a majority of civilian motorworks. dkzcivilianpack.snowlion_beta.name: Millitary Clay-colored DKZ M550 Snowlion
dkzcivilianpack.snowlion_beta.description:
Introducing the SnowKatt's military half-brother, the M550 SnowLion! With a larger frame, this german-inspired halftrack is capable of mounting beds for armaments, personel, cargo or fluids, and is sure to satisfy a multitude of roles.
 
Requires:

Beds:
- Crate Bed
- Tall Crate Bed
- Anti-Aircraft Bed
- Transport Bed
- Tanker Bed

dkzcivilianpack.ragingseagull_courageous.name: DKZ Raging Seagull MK.1 [820th Squadron: Courageous]
dkzcivilianpack.ragingseagull_courageous.description:
Take to the skies in the DKZ Raging Seagull MK.1! This classic stringbag is based off the Fairey Swordfish, an iconic biplane that sunk the Bismark! Capable of mounting 6 250lb bomb drop units, 2 60lb rocket quad-rail units, tailgunner's 308 Swarm mount, and the 750kg torpedo drop unit under the fuselage. Arm up to rain terror on the enemies, and fly triumphantly through the skies!

Requires:
- Bristol Pegasus Engine
- Raging Seagull Propeller

Optional:
- Titanus Torpedo Drop Unit
- 250lb Hailstorm Bomb Drop Unit [x6]
- 60lb Lightning Rocket Rails [x2]

dkzpartspack.dkz_alq_144.description: The ALQ-144 and 147 IRCM produced a pattern of pulses that was approximately synchronized with the rotation rate of these reticles. dwtmtspack.dvc2001d15_emeraldtrim.name: 2001 DVC D-15 - Emerald Custom
dwtmtspack.dvc2001d15_emeraldtrim.description: The 2001 DVC D-15 pickup is the medium-duty entry for DVC's D-Series of medium to heavy duty pickup trucks. This version of the D-15 comes equipped with a standard two-door cab and a rear leaf spring suspension configuration. And like all of the D-Series trucks, the D-15s come equipped with 4WD as a standard feature. Nevertheless, these trucks are capable of pulling a fair-sized load and are just a great daily-driver as well.

dwtmtspack.dvc2002olivier_trim1.description: The 2002 Olivier sedan is an AWD, midsize sedan option from DVC. This car was one of DVC's first all-original vehicle designs, and as per usual with DVC, is a reliable and capable vehicle. This vehicle, like the Stanley, is very popular as a fleet vehicle, and it's AWD performance makes it an especially big favorite with law enforcement agencies.

dwtmtspack.dvc2002wolf_trim1.name: 2002 DVC Wolf - Light Blue
dwtmtspack.dvc2002wolf_trim1.description: The 2002 DVC Wolf is DVC's first attempt as a performance vehicle. While the car itself isn't a full-blown performance car, rather DVC labels it as a muscle car, it still manages to perform well and look good at the same time. Rico Oliver (DVC's CEO) was especially proud that his company had come far enough to start dipping their toes into the performance vehicle market. This car has plenty of room for large engines, is RWD only, and is both reliable and comfortable to drive every day.

general's_general_vehicles.c172s.name: Cessna 172S Skyhawk
general's_general_vehicles.c172s.description: The Cessna 172S was introduced in 1998 and is powered by a Lycoming IO-360-L2A producing 180 horsepower (134 kW). The maximum engine rpm was increased from 2,400 rpm to 2,700 rpm resulting in a 20 hp (15 kW) increase over the R model. As a result, the maximum takeoff weight was increased to 2,550 lb (1,157 kg). This model is marketed under the name Skyhawk SP, although the Type Certification data sheet specifies it is a 172S.The 172S is built primarily for the private owner-operator and is, in its later years, offered with the Garmin G1000 avionics package and leather seats as standard equipment.

general's_general_vehicles.kawasaki_js40.name: Kawasaki JS-400 Jet Ski
general's_general_vehicles.kawasaki_js40.description: With the introduction of the Jet Ski, Kawasaki, in cooperation with aftermarket companies and enthusiasts, helped in creating the United States Jet Ski Boating Association (USJSBA). In 1982 the name was changed to the International Jet Sports Boating Association (IJSBA). At the start, only JS440 stand-ups were raced. After Kawasaki introduced the runabout style X2 in 1986 it gained its own class, later to be renamed the Sport Class.

general's_general_vehicles.nissan_s30z.name: Nissan Fairlady S30Z
general's_general_vehicles.nissan_s30z.description: The Fairlady Z was introduced in late 1969 as a 1970 model, with the L20 2.0-litre straight-six SOHC engine, rear-wheel drive, and a stylish coupe body. The engine, based on the Datsun 510's four-cylinder, produced 130 PS (96 kW; 128 hp) JIS and came with a four- or a five-speed manual transmission.

general's_general_vehicles.toyota_1-g-fe.description: The DOHC 1G-FE uses a narrow valve angle and other fuel economy optimizations. It was introduced in 1988, it features a cast iron block with aluminum cylinder head.

general's_general_vehicles.toyota_1-jz.name: Toyota 1JZ-GE Inline 6 engine
general's_general_vehicles.toyota_1-jz.description: Toyota JZ engine family is a series of inline-6 automobile engines. A replacement for the M-series inline-6 engines, the JZ engines were 24-valve DOHC engines. The JZ engine was offered in 2.5- and 3.0-litre versions.

general's_general_vehicles.toyota_2gd-ft.name: Toyota 2GD-FTV 2.4 Liter Inline 4 Turbo Diesel Engine
general's_general_vehicles.toyota_2gd-ft.description: The 2GD-FTV is a 2.4L straight-four common rail diesel engine with a variable nozzle turbocharger used in Generation 8 HILUX Gen 2 Fortuner Innova and Kijang Innova

general's_general_vehicles.toyota_2l-te.name: Toyota 2L-TE(II) Inline Turbo Diesel Engine
general's_general_vehicles.toyota_2l-te.description: The 2L-TE(II) is an upgrade of the 2L-TE. Of the same dimensions as the 2L-TE engine, the most significant change is that the camshaft lifts the valve directly via tappet instead of a rocker arm. The valve clearance is adjusted using shims. Compression ratio is also increased to 21.0:1, slightly higher than the 2L-T and 2L-TE. Maximum horsepower is 97 PS (71 kW; 96 hp) at 3800rpm and maximum torque ranges from 22.5 kg?m (221 N?m; 163 lb?ft) to 24.5 kg?m (240 N?m; 177 lb?ft) at 2400rpm.

general's_general_vehicles.toyota_4af_en.name: Toyota 4AF engine
general's_general_vehicles.toyota_4af_en.description: The fuel injected 4A-FE is the successor of the carbureted 4A-F. It was manufactured between 1987?2001. Toyota designed this engine with fuel economy in mind.

helicopterpack.ah64_black.name: Black AH-64 Apache
helicopterpack.ah64_black.description: [Engine: GE T700] The AH-64 Apache is the most lethal attack helicopter ever built. It features twin turboshaft engines and a variety of armaments, including a 30mm machine gun and pylons for hellfire missiles or hydra rocket pods. It seats two pilots in a 'tandem' front-back arrangement.

It seats two pilots in a 'tandem' front-back arrangement.

It seats two pilots in a 'tandem' front-back arrangement.

helicopterpack.ch47_green.name: Green CH-47 Chinook
helicopterpack.ch47_green.description: [Engine: Lycoming T55] The Boeing CH-47 'Chinook' is a medium-heavy lift helicopter first used in Vietnam. It features tandem contra-rotating rotors that give it plenty of power and remove the need for a tail rotor. Its ability to carry large amounts of troops and cargo made it a key asset for militaries around the world. Take note, though! This helicopter needs plenty of space to land, so make sure to clear out a helipad large enough for it.'

helicopterpack.ec145_black.name: Black Eurocopter 145
helicopterpack.ec145_black.description: [Engine: Turbomeca 1E2] The Eurocopter 145 is twin-turboshaft light to medium utility helicopter. This mod's version is configured to seat six, with two pilot seats and 2 rows of 2 passenger seats or storage items. A very versatile and reliable helicopter.

helicopterpack.r22_blue.name: Blue Robinson R22
helicopterpack.r22_blue.description: [Engine: Lycoming O-320] The Robinson R22 is reciprocating engine helicopter used as a trainer or very light utility helicopter. It doesn't have much power, but its minimal design makes it somehow capable of flight. Instructors often use it for teaching because of the philosophy, 'If you can fly this, you can fly anything!'.

helicopterpack.uh1_green.name: Green UH-1 Huey
helicopterpack.uh1_green.description: [Engine: Lycoming T-53] The UH-1 'Huey' was one of the most prolific military helicopters ever built. Its turboshaft engine allowed it to function as the first true medium utility helicopter, and it's still used today for training and utility purposes. This mod's version is configured to seat 10, with two pilot seats and space for 8 seats or crates in the back. Unlike the EC145, this helicopter has gunner's seats!

mai.owl_black.name: Owl, Night Black, White
mai.owl_black.description:
The M.A.I Owl, inspired by the Leyland Leopard bus, is perfect for transporting people around your cities! (To change the destination blind, write your destination on a name tag and right click on a hitbox, e.g the handle in the driver's cab) 
 Recommended parts: I4 diesel engine, standard truck wheels (IAV), standard seat (driver) (IAV), bus seats (passengers) (UNU)

mai.penguin_black.name: Penguin, Night Black
mai.penguin_black.description:
The M.A.I Penguin - affordable luxury. Inspired by the Jaguar E-type series I and powered by an i6 engine, the Penguin is both serious and fun! To pop the bonnet, press the 3rd button from the right on the dash. 
 Recommended parts: IAV low-end gasoline I6 engine, IAV standard car seats, IAV standard car wheels, MAI 2x7 ZV plate

mai.seagull_black.name: Seagull 36, Night Black
mai.seagull_black.description:
Sail the seven seas with the M.A.I Seagull 36, a 36 footer yacht with two (not currently usable) berths in the cabin for overnight trips, or enough seating for four or six at a push if you're only going out for the day! Thanks to TheOddlySeagull of Trin and DrProfLuigi of UNU for helping with this model 
 Recommended parts: IAV boat engine, Trin RV furniture, IAV None seats

mai.stork_black.name: Stork, Night Black
mai.stork_black.description:
The M.A.I Stork is perfect for any company that needs to move heavy objects. This is just the chassis, use convention compatible beds to transform it into a usable truck! 
 Recommended parts: IAV Truck wheels, IAV I4 diesel engine, IAV Standard seats, MAI ZV Style plates, Convention compatible truck beds

 Recommended parts: IAV Truck wheels, IAV I4 diesel engine, IAV Standard seats, MAI ZV Style plates, Convention compatible truck beds

mtsofficialpack.bell47g.name: Bell 47G
mtsofficialpack.bell47g.description: The Bell 47G is a simple, yet versatile helicopter.  While it only seats two, it can carry cargo or extra fuel in optional external containers, making it ideal for either short cargo flights or medium trips to remote bases.  Small guns may also be mounted to the fuselage, though these can only fire the direction the helicopter is facing.  As such, they are not recommended against 'hot' ground targets.

mtsofficialpack.comanche_blue.name: Blue Comanche
mtsofficialpack.comanche_blue.description: The Comanche is a small, swift, twin-engine craft.  While the lower wing might pose a hazard on overgrown runways, it makes up for it by being faster and nimbler than other planes of its size.

mtsofficialpack.e500_blue.name: Blue Eclipse 500
mtsofficialpack.e500_blue.description: The Eclipse 500, first flown in 2002, created a new class of aircraft: the very light jet, or VLJ. The MTS version is configured to seat five, with the pilot in the front and four passengers behind them. A great addition to any private airport, and quite efficient for its capacity and speed as well.

mtsofficialpack.firetruck.name: Fire Truck
mtsofficialpack.firetruck.description: The 1973 Ward LaFrance P80 Ambassador is a small fire truck, mostly known for being on the TV show Emergency!  This rendition seats two, and comes equipped with a working siren and emergency lights.  A must-have for any town!

mtsofficialpack.ft17_blue.name: Blue Renualt FT
mtsofficialpack.ft17_blue.description: The Renault FT (frequently referred to in post-World War I literature as the FT-17, FT17, or similar) was a French light tank that was among the most revolutionary and influential tank designs in history.  Although hoplessly outclassed by modern tanks, the FT17 is still a formidable threat against infantry and lightly-armored vehicles.

mtsofficialpack.pzlp11.name: PZL P11.c
mtsofficialpack.pzlp11.description: The PZL P11.c is a born and bred fighter aircraft. Its shoulder wing monoplane configuration provides the pilot with exceptional visibility of the sky and ground, and makes the PZL P11.c much faster than it's biplane fighter counterparts.

mtsofficialpack.scout_blue.name: Blue Scout
mtsofficialpack.scout_blue.description: The International Harvester Scout is an off road two door SUV made from 1961-1980. This SUV, the Scout II, was produced from 1971-1980. It seats two, with area for cargo in the back.

mtsofficialpack.trimotor_black.name: Black Ford Trimotor
mtsofficialpack.trimotor_black.description: The Ford Trimotor is an old, yet trustworthy aircraft.  Its large wingspan provides ample lift for short takeoffs, as well as enough to maintain flight with one engine out.  With room for 12 passengers or crates, it's a great choice for long-haul flights where reliability (but not time) is of the essence.

potatpacc.bleriot.name: Blériot XI
potatpacc.bleriot.description: The Blériot XI is a French aircraft of the pioneer era of aviation.It was produced in both single- and two-seat versions, powered by several different engines, and was widely used for competition and training purposes. Military versions were bought by many countries, continuing in service until after the outbreak of World War I in 1914.

potatpacc.f104_belg.name: F-104 Starfighter,Belgian (By Cactus)
potatpacc.f104_belg.description: The Lockheed F-104 Starfighter is a single-engine, supersonic interceptor aircraft which was extensively deployed as a fighter-bomber during the Cold War. Created as a day fighter by Lockheed as one of the Century Series of fighter aircraft for the United States Air Force (USAF), it was developed into an all-weather multirole aircraft in the early 1960s and produced by several other nations, seeing widespread service outside the United States.

sausesaigpfdpack.instrument_aircraft_80s.name: Boeing 737-300/757-300 PFD
sausesaigpfdpack.instrument_aircraft_80s.description: First introduced with the Boeing 737-300 in 1984, this flight display was one of Boeing's first and was later used in the 757-300 series. Indicates the attitude and airspeed of the plane.

sausesaigpfdpack.instrument_aircraft_pfd.name: Boeing 'ND' PFD
sausesaigpfdpack.instrument_aircraft_pfd.description: First intruduced with the 747-400 in 1989, this flight display is one of the most iconic ones made to date. Boeing put this PFD on a wide range of planes, including the 737 NG series, the 747-400 and 747-8, and the 777 series. Indicates the airspeed, altitude, climb rate, heading, and attitude of the plane.

sausesaigpfdpack.instrument_aircraft_shi.name: JPG of a PFD
sausesaigpfdpack.instrument_aircraft_shi.description: Rolls PFD on rolling, and translates it on speed. Why? Because JPG! [Originally was supposed to go in IVV, but cowboy said no :( ]

unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_a.name: §3UNU 'A' Frame
unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_a.description:
A cheap, yet durable car frame, primarily used in the UNU Bottom-Line series.

With solid axles, leaf springs, and rear drum brakes, this frame is only used in the most bare-bones cars.

unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_b.name: §3UNU 'B' Frame
unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_b.description:
A well-built car frame used in many UNU Mid-Tier vehicles.

Boasting 4-wheel disk brakes, fully independent suspension, a rear-mounted transmission, and sturdy axle housings, this frame can be found in most of UNU's civilian vehicles.

unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_c.name: §3UNU 'C' Frame
unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_c.description:
A modified version of the 'A' Frame, initially developed for military scout vehicles, and later used in UNU Civilian trucks.

This frame features 4-wheel-drive, in addition to the simple construction of the well-known 'A' Frame. Perfect for durable trucks on battlefields and work sites alike.

unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_pass.name: §3UNU G4 Frame (drivable)
unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_pass.description:
§lRecommended parts:§r

unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_t.name: §3UNU 'T' Frame
unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_t.description: The standard industrial truck frame. This frame can be found under buses, delivery trucks, firetrucks, and many other trucks that serve as the backbones of fleets across the world.

unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_u.name: §3UNU 'U' Frame
unuparts.unuparts_vehicle_unu_frame_u.description: The 'U' Frame is really just the 'T' Frame with an extra axle.
